---
title: GoCD - Continuous Delivery
title_tag_of_header: "Open Source Continuous Delivery and Automation Server | GoCD"
meta_description: "GoCD is an open source continuous delivery server that helps organizations increase productivity and deliver high quality through automation."
meta_keywords: "GoCD, continuous delivery, continuous delivery tool, continuous integration, continuous integration software, open source, automated release management, automation, software deployment"
---
<header class="banner">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="banner_heading">
      <h1>Simplify Continuous Delivery</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="banner-row-box">
      <div class="banner-row-box_item_image">
        <%= image_tag "home/ui_illo.svg", {:title => "GoCD illustration", :alt => "GoCD Value Stream Map", :class => 'ui-illo'} %>
      </div>
      <div class="banner-row-box_item_text">
        <h2>
          EASILY MODEL AND VISUALIZE COMPLEX WORKFLOWS WITH GoCD, A FREE AND OPEN SOURCE CONTINUOUS DELIVERY SERVER.
        </h2>
        <%= link_to 'GETTING STARTED GUIDE', "/getting-started/part-1/index.html", {:class => "btn btn-getting-started", "analytics-label" => "home-started-cta"} %>
        <%= link_to 'DOWNLOAD GoCD', "/download/index.html", {:class => "btn btn-download", "analytics-label" => "home-download-cta"} %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<section class="sub-banner">
  <div class="container">
    <h3>Free Webinar : Actionable Continuous Delivery Metrics : July 26</h3>
    <%= link_to 'REGISTER NOW', 'https://info.thoughtworks.com/Actionable_CD_Metrics.html' %>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="secondary-heading-section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="secondary-heading">
      Automate and streamline your build-test-release cycle for reliable, continuous delivery of your product.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="feature-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row-box-three">
      <div class="row-box-three_item">
        <%= partial "partials/whygocdfeature1" %>
      </div>
      <div class="row-box-three_item">
        <%= partial "partials/whygocdfeature2" %>
      </div>
      <div class="row-box-three_item">
        <%= partial "partials/whygocdfeature3" %>
      </div>
    </div>
    <%= link_to 'See more GoCD features', '/why-gocd/index.html', :class => 'btn btn-default see-all-features', "analytics-label" => "link_homepage_see_more_gocd_features" %>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="community-section">
  <div class="container row-box-two">
    <div class="row-box-two_item">
      <figure class="row-box-icon">
        <%= image_tag "icons/go.cd_plugins.svg", {:title => "GoCD open source plugins", :alt => "GoCD open source plugins"} %> 
      </figure>
      <div class="row-box-text">
        <h3 class="row-box-title">Plugins</h3>
      <p class="row-boxd-desc">
        GoCD has numerous extension points for which plugins can be created. There are
        <%= link_to 'numerous plugins', '/plugins/index.html', "analytics-label" => "link_homepage_plugins" %> 
        already available, or if you don't see
        what you need, you can <%= link_to 'write your own', 'https://developer.gocd.org/current/writing_go_plugins/go_plugins_basics.html',
                                    "analytics-label" => "link_homepage_plugin_writing_docs" %>
      </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row-box-two_item">
      <figure class="row-box-icon">
        <%= image_tag "icons/go.cd_community.svg", {:title => "GoCD open source community", :alt => "GoCD open source community"}  %>
      </figure>
      <div class="row-box-text">
        <h3 class="row-box-title">Community</h3>
        <p class="row-boxd-desc">
          GoCD's community is 1000 members strong and growing. Through our active forum, users and contributors share best practices and
          openly discuss a wide range of topics including product how-tos. To join in the
          conversation visit <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/go-cd" analytics-label="link_homepage_google_group" >our Google group.</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="support-banner-section"> 
  <%= partial "partials/supportbanner" %>
</section>



